author: USA TODAY, Joshua Bote, USA TODAY
title: A New Jersey doctor is the first emergency physician to die from coronavirus in the US
description: Frank Gabrin, 60, died in his husband's arms just days after he developed symptoms consistent with the virus. He was a two-time cancer survivor.
content:
HACKENSACK, N.J. An East Orange General Hospital doctor on Wednesday became the first emergency physician to die from likely coronavirus complications, the American College of Emergency Physicians said in a statement.
